author: CNN
description: The Justice Department says it has transmitted records related to the late convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein to the House Oversight Committee. This comes in response to its subpoena issued by the committee to the DOJ for Epstein records. The committee has said that it planned to make records public after receiving materials from DOJ, but would review the files first to ensure victims’ identities were redacted. #CNN #News
title: Epstein records transmitted to Congress, DOJ says

author: CNN
description: The Justice Department has released a transcript of the interview that Deputy Attorney General Todd Blanche conducted with Ghislaine Maxwell. #CNN #News
title: Ghislaine Maxwell’s interview transcript and audio released by DOJ

author: CNN
description: A tour bus carrying around 50 people east of Buffalo has overturned. Multiple fatalities, injuries, and entrapments have been reported, according to officials.
title: Multiple fatalities reported in NY bus crash

author: CNN
description: Multiple fatalities, including children, were reported Friday after a tour bus with about 50 passengers headed back to New York City from Niagara Falls crashed into a ditch, state police said. The bus rolled over after losing control for “unknown reasons,” injuring several people, New York State Police spokesperson James O’Callaghan said at a news conference. #CNN #News
title: Multiple fatalities & entrapments after tour bus crashes in NY state

author: CNN
description: Completed in 1912, the Kiruna Church has previously been named Sweden’s most beautiful building. Today, it’s part of a project which will see nearly 6,000 residents and a third of Kiruna’s buildings relocated over the next two decades. #travel #architecture #CNN #News
title: See how a whole church was moved across a city in Sweden

author: CNN
description: The state of Florida painted over a rainbow crosswalk outside the Pulse nightclub in Orlando, which commemorated the 49 people killed at the nightclub in 2016. The removal comes during campaigns by the state and Trump administration to paint over “asphalt art.” The dual directives are calling this a safety measure to make roads easier to navigate without distractions. #CNN #news #rainbowcrosswalk #pulsenightclub #florida
title: Rainbow crosswalk outside of Pulse nightclub removed

author: CNN
description: Dr. Elisabeth Potter went viral in January with a video detailing her frustrations over an experience with United Healthcare. Since posting the video, she says she has not been able to secure contracts with major health insurers and is now in danger of losing her surgery center. The health insurer says its decision not to let her facility in-network had nothing to do with her video and is not “penalizing” her for speaking out. #CNN #News
title: She spoke out about health insurance. Now, this doctor says she could lose her business

author: CNN
description: AK-47 demos, "trench candle" making and sock knitting were some of the activities citizens participated in during Russia's national flag day. CNN's Fred Pleitgen reports from Moscow at an event that encouraged patriotism to aid Russia's efforts on the frontline. #CNN #news
title: Russians rally around the flag for soldiers on the frontlines

author: CNN
description: CNN Senior Justice Correspondent Evan Perez explains why the FBI is investigating John Bolton, a former national security advisor of President Trump. #cnn #news
title: Why is the FBI investigating John Bolton?

author: CNN
description: Parts of Gaza are officially experiencing a “man-made” famine, according to a Friday report by a United Nations-backed initiative, which added that the situation is expected to worsen after months of relentless conflict. While some people have died of starvation and hunger, others have been killed trying to receive aid at distribution sites run by the controversial US- and Israeli-backed Gaza Humanitarian Foundation (GHF), which was brought in place to replace a UN system long criticized by Israel. #CNN #News
title: Gaza Humanitarian Foundation spokesman on the new aid reservation system

author: CNN
description: The job market is on such shaky ground that the Federal Reserve may soon need to cut interest rates, Fed Chair Jerome Powell said at annual economic symposium. CNN's Vanessa Yurkevich explains how the Fed is looking at the current US economy. #cnn #news #politics
title: Fed Chair signals rate cuts are coming

author: CNN
description:
Two lawsuits were filed against Delta and United Airlines on Tuesday after passengers paid extra money for window seats that didn't have any windows.
 #CNN #News #delta #united
title: Delta, United sued for selling windowless ‘window seats’

author: CNN
description: An indictment of New York City Mayor Eric Adams’ former top advisor came a day after another member of Adams’ inner circle became embroiled in a bizarre apparent bribery attempt involving a news reporter and an empty bag of potato chips. CNN’s Gloria Pazmino reports on the back-to-back incidents as Adams seeks reelection. #cnn #news #ericadams
title: Former aide to NYC mayor gives reporter cash in bag of chips

author: CNN
description: Stocks surged Friday after Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell suggested a rate cut could be coming soon. #CNN #News
title: DOW soars into record territory as Powell hints at rate cut

author: CNN
description: The FBI conducted a court-authorized search at John Bolton’s home as part of a national security investigation into whether he disclosed classified information in his 2020 book, according to two people familiar with the matter. #CNN #News
title: Trump says he knows 'nothing' about search of Bolton’s home

author: CNN
description: Millions tuned into a livestream of rare deep-sea creatures off the coast of Argentina. This viral scientific mission even included a plump starfish resembling a beloved cartoon character. #cnn #science #ocean #underwater
title: Millions flock to livestream featuring rare deep-sea creatures

author: CNN
description: Asked about the search on Friday, Trump told reporters he knew “nothing about it.” But he added that he expected the Justice Department to brief him likely later in the day and suggested he had the power to initiate law enforcement moves. “I don’t want to know about it. It’s not necessary. I could know about it. I could be the one starting it, and I’m actually the chief law enforcement officer. But I feel that it’s better this way,” he said. #CNN #News
title: Trump: 'I know nothing about' Bolton's home, office searches by FBI

author: CNN
description: As international efforts to strike a peace deal between Russia and Ukraine continue to stall, CNN's Ben Wedeman visits Orikhiv, a town where residents are trying to survive in the ruins amid the constant threat of further Russian attacks.
title: Inside Ukraine's trenches as hopes for peace deal fade

author: CNN
description: The British government has agreed to pay almost $4 million to more than 7,000 Kenyans affected by a 2021 fire started during a military training exercise but won't accept liability for the incident. Locals say the blaze caused lasting health problems, destroyed property, and damaged the environment. #cnn #news
title: UK to pay $4M to Kenyan forest fire victims

author: CNN
description: Parts of Gaza are officially experiencing a “man-made” famine, according to a report by a United Nations-backed initiative. Israeli authorities rejected the report, saying it “relies on partial, biased data and superficial information originating from Hamas.” Meanwhile testimony and images from aid groups and the UN show malnutrition has been present in Gaza for months.
title: Man-made famine confirmed in Gaza, UN-backed initiative says

author: CNN
description: “The White Lotus” star Jason Isaacs sits down with CNN’s Elizabeth Wagmeister to discuss his Emmy nomination, fan theories and whether he might be returning for Season 4 of the HBO show. #CNN #News
title: Jason Isaacs on His Emmy Nom, Possible 'White Lotus' Spinoff & Third Season of 'The OA'

author: CNN
description: A federal judge has ordered the remote detention camp in the Florida Everglades known as “Alligator Alcatraz” to no longer take additional detainees and remove additional infrastructure added to the site. CNN's Isabel Rosales reports. #CNN #News
title: Federal judge bans 'Alligator Alcatraz' from taking new detainees

author: CNN
description: The FBI conducted a court-authorized search at John Bolton’s home as part of a national security investigation, according to a person familiar with the matter. CNN observed FBI personnel near the former US national security adviser’s house in the Washington, DC, area. FBI were seen speaking to a person on the porch of the house, and at least four to six agents were seen going inside. #CNN #News
title: FBI conducts search at John Bolton’s home

author: CNN
description: A Brisbane postman has been hailed as a 'laundry hero' after being caught on camera taking a woman's laundry in from the rain. Homeowner Verrity Wandel's video of Gurpreet Singh's act of kindness quickly went viral. “If you have the opportunity to do a totally selfless act, do it, don’t think about it," she said.
title: ‘Hero’ Postman Rescues Laundry From Rain

author: CNN
description: Cracker Barrel’s recent rebrand and makeover sparked online outrage, with some parts of the MAGA right calling the changes “woke.” Van Lathan explains why he is frustrated people are stuck in "another culture war when real stuff is going on." The CNN NewsNight panel debates the chain's logo change. #CNN #News
title: 'Brother Barrel, go all the way' Van Lathan reacts to Cracker Barrel logo change

author: CNN
description: For the first time since sending troops to fight in Ukraine, North Korea is publicly confirming combat deaths, an abrupt reversal after months of silence and denial. State media broadcast an emotional ceremony featuring Kim Jong Un, troops honored for valor, and families of more than 100 fallen "heroes." #cnn #northkorea #russia #ukraine
title: North Korea admits its troops died in Russia's war

author: CNN
description: One mom shares how her family’s life was changed when they discovered Bill Brown’s nonprofit food bank in Bronson, Florida.
title: This 96-year-old's food bank offers much more than food

author: CNN
description: At a meet-and-greet with law enforcement in Washington, DC, Trump vowed to re-turf the capital’s parks, declaring that no one knows more about grass than him.
title: Trump: ‘I know more about grass than any human being’

author: CNN
description:
At 10 years old, brainiac Sean the Science Kid already has plenty in common with Dr. Sanjay Gupta: He loves to learn and explain science to his million-plus Instagram followers. They discuss their shared love of the brain—and Sean takes the mic to ask Dr. Gupta some of his own questions.

Listen to the full episode on CNN's Chasing Life podcast: https://link.chtbl.com/Rbf2HhVZ

#CNN #News #Health #Science
title: Exploring the brain with 10-year-old 'Sean the Science Kid' | Chasing Life

author: CNN
description: Cracker Barrel has unveiled a new logo, but the rebrand is not sitting well with many of its customers. CNN's Laura Coates discusses the controversial logo change with a with a brand design specialist. #cnn #crackerbarrel #logo
title: Backlash over Cracker Barrel's logo change

author: CNN
description: A California parole board has denied parole for Erik Menendez, who was convicted alongside his brother Lyle of murdering their parents in 1989, delivering a crippling blow to the brothers’ yearslong fight for release. CNN’s Brianna Keilar speaks to LA Times reporter James Queally, the only journalist at the 10-hour parole hearing, on what this means.
title: Erik Menendez denied parole, decades after parents' murder

author: CNN
description: CNN senior data analyst Harry Enten shows how President Donald Trump benefitted from mail-in voting in the 2024 election, despite his recent efforts to curtail the process in future elections.
title: Trump doubles down on call to end mail-in voting method that helps him

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump joined law enforcement in DC for hamburgers and pizza Thursday. Last week, Trump ordered the federal government to take control of DC’s police department and deployed National Guard troops. Trump teased earlier in the day that he planned to join law enforcement in the streets of DC, though he appeared to scrap those plans for a more standard meet-and-greet with those he has deployed.
title: Trump visited law enforcement at a US Park Police facility in Washington, DC

author: CNN
description: In separate incidents, Villanova University and University of Tennessee at Chattanooga were each targeted by reports of an active shooter on campus, both of which turned out to be a hoax.
title: Active shooter hoaxes target two universities

author: CNN
description: 75-year-old Donna Adelson is facing murder charges in the death of her former son-in-law, Florida State University law professor Dan Markel, who was killed by two hit men in 2014. CNN's Jean Casarez reports on the details that led to Adelson's arrest and trial, where she is accused of being the mastermind behind the murder-for-hire plot.
title: This 75-year-old is on trial for a 2014 murder. The victim was her son-in-law

author: CNN
description: CNN's Anderson Cooper speaks with Alec Luhn, a hiker who was rescued after 6 days with little food and water on a remote mountaintop in Norway.
title: Hiker describes moment he was rescued after 6 days
